To address the issue where the mobile menu "does nothing" when clicked, I will modify the **Header** component to use a **high-priority overlay (Z-index 100)** for the mobile menu.

The previous issue was likely caused by "Z-index fighting" between the sticky header and the mobile menu container, making the menu appear behind the content or not register clicks.

I will also strictly enforce the **Desktop vs. Mobile** visibility rules you requested:
1.  **PC/Desktop:** The menu items (Home, Serviços, etc.) will be visible. The "three lines" button will be **completely hidden**.
2.  **Mobile:** The text menu will be hidden. The "three lines" button will be visible. Clicking it will open a full-screen menu that covers everything, ensuring it works.

